Definition 2.1. Given a map $p\colon Y\to X$, we say $p$ is semilocally 1-connected, or sl1c, if for all $y\in Y$ there is a basic open neighbourhood $U$ of $p(y)$ and a basic open neighbourhood $N$ of $y$ with $p(N)\subset U$ such that for any square
